cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the vulnerability of deep learning classifiers to adversarial examples and proposes a method to bypass statistical detection of such examples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a new attack method, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
